title: @everyone angry at andi
body:
Look, here’s the thing.

When she told Jonah that he didn’t have to do anything if he didn’t want to, she was really irritated. Like, let’s be honest: Jonah is the type of guy that wants to be in a relationship, but doesn’t want to put any actual effort into that relationship. And Andi was sick and tired of hearing him complain about how much work it all was, and what she meant there was “just break up with Amber if you don’t want to date her.” Jonah doesn’t have a great track record with commitment, and Andi is among one of the people that he’s ended up hurting. So of course she was more than a little ticked off at Jonah’s actions. It’s not his fault that he doesn’t want to deal with a relationship, but it’s not fair of him to keep leading Amber on, so to speak.

And it really wasn’t fair of Jonah to bail on Andi. Costume Day is something she’s really passionate about. There aren’t many activities at that school that appeal to Andi - Buffy is athletic and into sports (as are Marty and TJ), Jonah is popular and enjoys Ultimate Frisbee, and even Cyrus gets really into film-making sometimes - but this is basically a high-stakes craft project. Andi has done so much for Jonah (the Space Otters, “I’m not really into labels,” everything with Amber, etc.), and it seems only fair that he do something for her in turn. Not only that, but Andi just found out that her parents had cancelled their wedding and was really broken up about it. That was something that meant a lot to her, and she was still reeling at what felt to her like betrayal. To have Jonah misconstrue the meaning of words like that, and to turn them back on her…of course she felt abandoned, and of course she was angry. She had a right to be.

summary: I'm seeing so many new andi mack fans on twitter! so many ppl being 'i just started andi mack and it's so good!' and then...
question: I'm seeing so many new andi mack fans on twitter! so many ppl being 'i just started andi mack and it's so good!' and then sharing it w their friends ugh warms my heart i hope disney are seeing this
answer: Unfortunately the disappointing part of this remains that pretty much all of these new fans are having to catch up by watching the series through illegal methods, because it’s still not available on any legitimate streaming services (older episodes aren’t even on DisneyNOW anymore) - meaning that any new fans the show is gaining right now isn’t actually benefiting the numbers or ratings, or helping Disney in any way financially, etc. Disney may be seeing an increased interest on social media (especially following 311 and being aware of the FBE video) but they’re still screwing themselves over by making the series unavailable to most people.

body:
I know we are all sad, and most of us are probably listening to angsty songs about Tyrus, but please listen to Lucky by Hoobastank. I happened to stumble across it today and it just fits them perfectly. Its a song that would be from Tj’s point of view and its such a cute song!

Also, I’m not good at making video edits, but if someone did a Tyrus video using this song that’d be amazing 😍😊

If you want another song that goes with the angst from 3x13 though, The Reason by Hoobastank kinda fits that situation.
